{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2015}} {{Infobox academic | caption = Solomon Adlivankin | name = Solomon Adlivankin | image = Solomon_Adlivankin.jpg | birth_date = {{Birth date|df=yes|1922|12|29}} | birth_place = [[Minsk]], [[Byelorussian Soviet Socialist Republic|BSSR]] | death_date = {{Death date|df=yes|1985|04|14}} | death_place = [[Perm]], [[Russian Soviet Federative Socialist Republic|RSFSR]] (now Russia) | residence = | job = | academic_degree = | academic_status = | main_interests = [[Linguistics]], [[phonetics]], [[dialectology]], [[Old Church Slavonic|Old Slavonic language]] | alma_mater = [[Saratov State University]] (1946) | doctoral_advisor = | awards = [[Conspicuous Gallantry Medal]],<ref>From interview with Vera Shahova-Adlivankina: Из интервью с вдовой С. Ю. Адливанкина Верой Лукьяновной Шаховой-Адливанкиной.</ref> Medal for [[Victory Day (9 May)|Victory]] over Germany in the [[Eastern Front (World War II)|Great Patriotic War]] (1941–1945) | website = }}
'''Solomon Juryevich (correct: Uravich) Adlivankin''' ({{lang-ru|link=no|Соломóн Ю́рьевич (correct: У́равич) Адливáнкин}}, {{IPA-ru|səlɐˈmon ˈurʲɪvʲɪtɕ ɐdʲlʲɪˈvankʲɪn}}) was a Soviet [[Linguistics|linguist]], the Dean of philological faculty at [[Perm State University]] (1967–1971), the author of [[handbook]]s on [[Old Church Slavonic|Old Slavonic]] [[Phonetics]], unique in the 1970s ; he was one of the Perm derivatology school founders, also he took part in compiling [[Akchim River|Akchim]] [[Dialectology|dialect]] dictionary.<ref>Franciska Skitova on Solomon Adlivankin and his work: Скитова Ф. И вспоминаем благодарно… // А жизнь — одна и неразъятна. Воспоминания о Соломоне Юрьевиче Адливанкине. Пермь: Издательский центр «Титул», 2011. С. 24–25</ref>
==Sources== * Solomon Adlivankin at Russian Wikipedia: [[:ru:Адливанкин, Соломон Юрьевич|Адливанкин, Соломон Юрьевич]] // Википедия, свободная энциклопедия. * The Memoirs of Solomon Adlivankin: А жизнь — одна и неразъятна. Воспоминания о Соломоне Юрьевиче Адливанкине. Пермь: Издательский центр «Титул», 2011. – 352 с., илл.[https://web.archive.org/web/20140625025652/http://tl.perm.ru/adliv]
