{{italic title}}
'''''Varlık''''' is a [[Turkey|Turkish]] literature and art magazine. Established by Yaşar Nabi Nayır in 1933, it often publishes poetry and works of famous Turkish poets and writers.

''Varlık'' has a unique significance  in [[Turkish literature]]. Most Turks who have become famous in literature have become so through publishing their works in ''Varlık'', such as [[Sait Faik Abasıyanık]]. Since 2001 the magazine has been a member of the [[Eurozine]] network.

